name: stillwater-wildlife-management-area-annual-water-management-plan-86650
notes: The primary goal of the annual water plan is to set a strategy for the most  efficient use of the available water delivered to Stillwater WMA. For all practical purposes, Fallon NWR no longer receives sufficient water from the Carson River to maintain any quality wetlands. Effects of the final Operating Criteria and Procedures (OCAP) and the 1987 and 1988 drought in Western Nevada have combined to seriously reduce flows to the WMA. A 100% water year is forecast for on-farm delivery but tight water management with a minimum of drain water flow is expected with a projected 32,500 AF delivery to Stillwater WMA. This is the 1980 plan.
